Definition.WordDefinition: skyrocket \sky"rock`et\ (sk[imac]"r[o^]k`[e^]t), v. i. To rise rapidly; -- usually used figuratively, as of prices. [PJC]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: skyrocket \sky"rock`et\ (sk[imac]"r[o^]k`[e^]t), n. A rocket that ascends high and burns as it flies; a species of fireworks. [1913 Webster]

skyrocket n 1: propels bright light high in the sky, or used to propel a lifesaving line or harpoon [syn: {rocket}] 2: sends a firework display high into the sky [syn: {rocket}] v : shoot up abruptly, like a rocket; "prices skyrocketed" [syn: {rocket}]
